The paper discusses the application of self-paced learning (SPL) in computer vision and pattern recognition tasks, which are typically covered under the arXiv sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the theoretical insights into SPL, which involves optimization algorithms and loss functions, which are typically covered under the arXiv sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.ST (Statistics). Additionally, the paper proposes a new loss function for SPL that is useful for weakly labeled large-scale data processing tasks, which is relevant to the arXiv sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
